cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about deep learning methods for semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning approaches, which suggests that it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses various applications of semantic segmentation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions autonomous driving, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper discusses virtual and augmented reality systems, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
